{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/nnc\/modelbuilder"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ModelBuilder","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:3NNC12ModelBuilderC","role":"symbol","title":"ModelBuilder","roleHeading":"Class","symbolKind":"class","modules":[{"name":"NNC"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ModelBuilder","kind":"identifier"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A model builder is a more generic type of model. A model can be quite static,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"thus, you have to be quite careful to have a model work with dynamic inputs."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You cannot use reshape, or anything that can generate fixed tensor outputs from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a fixed inputs."}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/init(_:name:)-4pup0","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/init(_:name:)-55gex"],"title":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/callAsFunction(_:inputs:_:streamContext:)-101bg","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/callAsFunction(_:inputs:_:streamContext:)-4i10p","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/callAsFunction(inputs:_:streamContext:)-4tnis","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/callAsFunction(inputs:_:streamContext:)-8pae9","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/compile(_:inputs:isEager:)-1lsvw","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/compile(_:inputs:isEager:)-8ge5z","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/compile(inputs:isEager:)-4kat6","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder\/compile(inputs:isEager:)-4yweq"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["Linux"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ModelBuilder","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"T","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A model builder on the other hand doesn’t have that restriction. When input changes,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it simply calls the given builder closure to construct a new model. In such way,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you can continue to use reshape etc to assume fixed inputs and outputs, it will just","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"work for dynamic inputs. The newly built model will carry over stateful components","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(parameters) from the old models, thus, it doesn’t reset your training. This also means","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you need to make sure parameter shape won’t change when input changes, otherwise we","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will fatal.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/ModelBuilder"},"kind":"symbol","relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/AnyModelBuilder"],"title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/NNC\/AnyModel"],"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships"}],"references":{"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/NNC/AnyModelBuilder":{"a